FBIS4-26624 "drchi122_b_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-122 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 United States & Canada Vice Premier Li Lanqing Meets U.S. Automaker Vice Premier Li Lanqing Meets U.S. Automaker OW2306124994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1235 GMT 23 Jun 94 OW2306124994 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, June 23 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing met here today with Wayne Booker, executive vice-president of Ford International automotive operations of the United States. Li spoke highly of the cooperation between Ford and the Chinese side, and said that there was great potential in China's auto industry. Booker and his party arrived here today at the invitation of the Ministry of Machinery Industry of China. During their stay in China, they will discuss cooperation in manufacturing auto components with relevant departments of China.
